# Phase 8: Admin Intelligence Suite

Build a powerful centralized control center for VibeStream administrators.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This phase modifies global authentication middleware and high-level RLS policies. It is critical to ensure that `is_admin` is only granted to trusted accounts.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] Database Layer
Update the database schema to support administrative roles and secure high-privilege operations.

#### [NEW] [admin-roles.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/admin-roles.sql)
SQL migration to add `is_admin` column and configure RLS.

---

### [Component] Authentication & Security
Implement server-side protection for administrative routes.

#### [NEW] [middleware.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/middleware.ts)
Implement Next.js middleware to intercept `/admin` routes and verify admin status.

---

### [Component] Admin Interface
Create the visual dashboard and management tools.

#### [NEW] [layout.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/(admin)/layout.tsx)
The administrative shell with a dedicated sidebar.

#### [NEW] [page.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/(admin)/dashboard/page.tsx)
Analytics dashboard showing platform-wide metrics.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `node scripts/test-admin-access.js` to verify middleware redirection.

### Manual Verification
- Log in as a regular user and attempt to access `/admin/dashboard` (should redirect to `/`).
- Use SQL to set an account as `is_admin = true` and access the dashboard (should succeed).
- Verify the user and video counts match the actual database state.
